				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 42 bard - puller?<a name="39747"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 04 8:32 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Pulling in LDoN is wonderful work for a bard.  I do it at 40.
<br />

<br />
You need
<br />

<br />
Kellin's Lugubrious Lament (level 8 song) to lull/pacify the mobs.  Works on mobs up to level 60.  A decent string instrument and good CHA help with resists (or at least keeping the mob from aggroing when they resist). Duration is long enough to pacify 2 mobs and pull a 3rd. 
<br />

<br />
Typically, I will pull with Selo's Consonant Chain (level 23 song) so the mob is slowed and snared while in bound. This gives the rest of the casters time to land a few debuffs, better slows.  Alternately, I use Fufil's Curtailing Chant (level 30) for the MR debuff.
<br />

<br />
Always, always, always keep your best mez song and charm ready.  If there is an overpull you can quickly lock down the adds.  If needed charm an add and send it after another add(or the main target).
<br />

<br />
Hard setting LDoNs are a bit trickier since the mobs resist Kellins a lot more.  There is a guide on that in the Guides section of this site.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
