				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 42 bard - puller?<a name="39783"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 04 11:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Since I did not get the whole swarm kiting down to a science I group exclusively LDon and this is how I was pulling at the lvl.
<br />

<br />
I was able to lull 3 mobs and pull the forth. If I was in a room that had more than four mobs I would lull 3 pull one switch and mez add on inc. This gave me time to through a few twist in for group to handle inc and me to keep add under control.
<br />

<br />
Now as for lull I have had critical failures with it at times. Just have to trust your healer and lock down as much as you can before bring to group get the adds finished there and take care of the others you have mezzed. I thought pulling was going to be boring as a Bard, but to be honest I love it. I have more fun figuring out how to break a room every time we move forward.
<br />

<br />
My song lineup for the 40 was the following
<br />

<br />
1 Mez 
<br />
2 Lull
<br />
3 group buff
<br />
4 group buff
<br />
5 group buff Or Snare/ slow depended on if we had a slower
<br />
6 group buff
<br />
7 Snare / slow if we had a slower and no snare. Other wise I keep the LoY song memmed in case someone was slowed or doted or Charm to add to dps.
<br />
8 Pull song / I used Syvelian's Anti-Magic Aria for pulling simple cause alot of the mobs were buffed
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps
<br />

<br />
Tuban
<br />
56 Song on Lanys</span></td>
