			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 42 bard - puller?<a name="39859"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 04 6:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Check out <a href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Guide.aspx?id=8&amp;ForumID=132">Anatomy of a Train:  A Newbie Guide to Aggro and Pulling</a>.
<br />

<br />
A couple of notes about pulling LDoNs (or anything else):
<br />

<br />
You do NOT have to be in LoS (Line of Sight) to sing your Lull song on a target.  That means that you can sneak up to a door or corner, JUST far enough to target the mob, then back up a little and sing your lull song, it will land.
<br />

<br />
You DO have to have LoS, (which means the mob's will too) to START your Dispell song to make the pull.  You can have the mob targetted from outside the door, but if you try to sing your Dispell song, unlike your Lull song, it will say, &quot;You cannot see your target&quot;.  At that point, poke yourself inside the door, JUST long enough to start the song, then RUN back to your group.  You do NOT have to be in LoS when the song LANDS.
<br />

<br />
Why all this about LoS?  Because the mob usually will not &quot;see&quot; you or target you until your song LANDS.  If the mob is a caster, they MUST establish LoS first before they can target you to cast.
<br />

<br />
So, you START your song, run back to your group, or around a corner real fast.  The caster mob, rather than stand in the next room and nuke you to oblivion, will RUN UP TO YOU to get LoS.  Then your tank can start smacking and taunting without bum rushing the room and aggroing the whole place.
<br />

<br />
A typical example of Lulling a room before a pull in LDoN, (Using Tak as example, since it seems to be the worst for aggroing through doors etc.):
<br />

<br />
Go up to the door, and open it, staying as far from it as you can, and still click it open.  F8 (or use the new &quot;cycle NPC&quot; key, if you mapped it).  Lull any mobs you can see from there.  Now nudge your self to one side, and forward a bit, and see if you can target any other mobs.  Nudge yourself to the other side, look in diagonally and lulling anything else you can see.  Once you have lulled everything you can see, step into the door, and see if you get jumped, lol.  Often, there are mobs just inside the doors that you CAN'T target from outside the room.  Often, that is your first pull, lol.  If you don't get jumped, target the one closest to the door, and START your dispell song, and run to your group.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
