				<td colspan="2"><span>Here is what I do, exactly at 44.
<br />

<br />
If there is no other haste class:
<br />

<br />
I lull the mobs in the room with the lament song.  I start close and work my way back, that way if it's resisted, there is a chance (sometimes very small, but still a chance) I won't get two or more.  After I select which one I want to pull, I inform the group, the cast Selo's chain.  This does get resisted about 10-20 percent of the time.  While running back to the group, I start singing amplification, then begin twisting in Berzerker Cressendo, Selo's Chain, and the old Brusco's Bellow(all singing).  After the tank has established aggro, I enter into melee while twisting the 4 songs.
<br />
I also have Mezz and Charm up in case (rarely happens though) one or more are pulled.
<br />

<br />
If we have a haste class. I use Selo's and my 3 chants. Using a drum and a weapon.
<br />
</span></td>
